{"actor":"Bernardo Kuri","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-06T20:41:36Z","event_type":"updated","id":117,"issue_id":"MCPROXY-auk","new_value":"{\"description\":\"## Current Problem\\n\\nSearch has 4 depth levels (0-3) with parameters: max_depth, brief, max_tools\\n\\nNow that schemas are removed from search (commit 5a4f543), depth levels feel unnecessary:\\n- depth=0: Server names only\\n- depth=1: Server names + categories + tool counts  \\n- depth=2: All above + tool names + truncated descriptions\\n- depth=3: All above + full descriptions\\n\\n## Proposed Solution\\n\\nSimplify to automatic behavior based on query:\\n\\n**Empty query:**\\n- Return server list with tool counts (current depth=1)\\n- No tool details, just discovery\\n\\n**Query provided:**\\n- Return matching tools with truncated descriptions (current depth=2)\\n- Limit to 5 tools per server by default (current max_tools default)\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n1. Remove parameters: max_depth, brief, max_tools\\n2. Simplify ManifestQuery.search() to automatic behavior\\n3. Update handlers.py to remove parameters from schema\\n4. Update help text\\n5. Test with agents to ensure discoverability remains good\\n\\n## Benefits\\n\\n- Simpler API for agents to understand\\n- Fewer parameters = less confusion\\n- Predictable behavior (no need to understand depth levels)\\n- Still covers all use cases (server discovery vs tool search)\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"MCPROXY-auk\",\"title\":\"Simplify search: remove depth levels, make behavior automatic\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"github@bkuri.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-07T02:41:04Z\",\"created_by\":\"Bernardo Kuri\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-07T02:41:04Z\"}"}
