{"actor":"Bernardo Kuri","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-06T20:50:28Z","event_type":"updated","id":129,"issue_id":"MCPROXY-s1j","new_value":"{\"priority\":2}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"MCPROXY-s1j\",\"title\":\"Adaptive TTL Learning - Track cache hits/misses/staleness to auto-recommend and adjust TTL values per tool\",\"description\":\"CONTEXT: Create self-optimizing cache that learns optimal TTL from usage patterns.\\n\\nREQUIREMENTS:\\n- Track per tool: cache_hits, cache_misses, hit_rate, staleness_events, avg_response_time\\n- TTL adjustment strategies:\\n  * Hit rate based: hit_rate \\u003e 0.8 → TTL * 1.5\\n  * Staleness aware: staleness_rate \\u003e 5% → TTL * 0.5\\n  * Cost aware: response_time \\u003e 1s → TTL * 2.0\\n- Combined learning: weighted average of strategies (40% hit_rate, 40% staleness, 20% cost)\\n- Learning modes: conservative (±10%), aggressive (±50%), hybrid\\n- Config: adaptive_ttl.enabled=true, .mode='hybrid', .min_ttl=30, .max_ttl=86400\\n\\nDEPENDENCIES: Cache System (MCPROXY-adt)\\n\\nACCEPTANCE:\\n- TTL recommendations accurate\\n- Auto-adjustment improves cache efficiency\\n- Learning doesn't cause oscillation\\n- Can disable auto-adjust, just show recommendations\\n\\nESTIMATED: 1.5 weeks\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":3,\"issue_type\":\"feature\",\"owner\":\"github@bkuri.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-07T02:21:09Z\",\"created_by\":\"Bernardo Kuri\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-07T02:21:09Z\"}"}
